text: Boeing Orbital Flight Test-2 (also known as Boe OFT-2) was a repeat of Boeing's failed first Orbital Flight Test (OFT-1) of its Starliner spacecraft. The uncrewed mission was part of NASA's Commercial Crew Program. The Starliner OFT-2 mission launched 19 May 2022 at 22:54:47 UTC or (6:54:47 PM EST) and it lasted one week. Starliner successfully docked with the International Space Station (ISS) on 21 May 2022 at 00:28 UTC or (8:28 PM EST). ==References== Category:May 2022 events
title: Boeing Orbital Flight Test 2
